Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on modeling ride requests and their variations over location and time, which can be considered as a social network problem. 
2. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the potential of ride pooling, which can have a significant impact on society and transportation systems. 
3. cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) - The paper analyzes real-world data from a ride-sharing service and models the spatial and temporal variability of ride requests, which can be considered as a social and economic network problem. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents an algorithm for automatic generation of synthetic ride request graphs, which can be considered as a data structures and algorithms problem. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses real-world data to model ride requests and their variations, which can be considered as a machine learning problem.
